    <description>Kalanjar (کلنجار) is an early Persian (Farsi) chatbot from the MS-DOS era (circa 1992-1993), created by Farhad Dadgostar at Isfahan University of Technology.

This package provides a convenient launcher that runs Kalanjar in DOSBox-X with proper Persian text rendering. The launcher automatically configures DOSBox-X to use text-mode output (OpenGL) for correct display of Persian text and TUI box-drawing characters.

Simply run 'kalanjar' from any directory to start the chatbot. The program will mount your current directory as C: and the Kalanjar installation as D:, then automatically launch the chatbot.

This is a historical preservation package - one of the earliest examples of Persian-language conversational AI.</description>
    <summary>Historic Persian DOS-era chatbot with DOSBox-X integration</summary>
    <tags>dos persian farsi chatbot ai dosbox-x historical preservation tui</tags>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/Foadsf/Kalanjar-DOS-preservation#license</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="dosbox-x" />
    </dependencies>
    <releaseNotes>## Version 1.1.0
- Fixed Persian text rendering by using OpenGL text-mode output
- Added automatic DOSBox-X detection from multiple installation sources
- Included both DOS (KLUDGE.EXE) and Windows XP wrapper versions
- No custom fonts or TSR loaders required
- Perfect rendering of Persian text and TUI box-drawing characters</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
